EnterWithNativeToken_Integration_Concrete_Test
├── given null
│  └── it should revert
└── given not null
   ├── given SETTLED status
   │  └── it should revert
   ├── given EXPIRED status
   │  └── it should revert
   └── given ACTIVE status
      ├── when msg value zero
      │  └── it should revert
      └── when msg value not zero
         ├── when token not WETH
         │  └── it should revert
         └── when token Weth
            ├── when sync changes status
            │  ├── when new status EXPIRED
            │  │  └── it should revert
            │  └── when new status SETTLED
            │     └── it should revert
            └── when sync not change status
               ├── given no adapter
               │  ├── it should wrap the native token into WETH
               │  ├── it should transfer tokens to the contract
               │  ├── it should mint share tokens to the caller
               │  └── it should emit an {Enter} event
               └── given adapter
                  ├── it should wrap the native token into WETH
                  ├── it should transfer tokens to the adapter
                  ├── it should stake via the adapter
                  ├── it should mint share tokens to the caller
                  └── it should emit {Enter} and {Stake} events
